<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence from members of Llandovery U3A Transport Group (TIC 090)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:14pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">Written evidence from</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt"> members of </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt">Llandovery</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt"> U3A</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt"> Transport Group (TIC 090)</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:14pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Summary</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">To describe existing passenger transport</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">To highlight the problems</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">To identify the people affected</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 28.52pt; padding-left:7.48pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">To suggest some solutions</span></li></ul><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 24pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none">1)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Background.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">This submission is based on Llandovery, Carmarthenshire, to highlight the public transport problems in this rural area. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The main form of transport, as in all rural areas, being the private car.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Transport is needed for employment, further educa</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">tion, hospital visits, entertainment and shopping.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The main problems are lack of transport combined with the lack of co-ordination between modes of transport resulting in difficulties</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> for both able and disabled members of the community.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 24pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Existing provision</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Llandovery is on the A40 and is served by:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Three bus routes via various villages to  Carmarthen</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 252pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">   Brecon</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 252pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">   Lampeter </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Heart of Wales railway line from Swansea to Shrewsbury via several small towns, with connections</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">to London from Swansea and the north a</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">nd the midlands from Shrewsbury.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">County Cars a volunteer run car service initiated by the WRVS for essential journeys  ie  hospital appointments.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">4)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Two private taxi services.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 24pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none">3)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Problems with the current infrastructure</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The low number of bus services </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">combined with the length of the journey and the limited time available for activities.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The poor links between train and bus for onward travel.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The non - existent connections between the town and neighbouring villages.  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Buses</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Carmarthen  - five per day dur</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ing school term, only three per day during school holidays. Duration 1hr 20 mins. Last service departs Carmarthen at 17.45</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">b)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Brecon  - three per day (Mon to Sat). Duration 40mins. Last service departs Brecon at 17.05</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">c)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Lampeter –   route A -  one service on Mo</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">nday </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">and Friday. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 108pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Route B – one service Mon, Tues, Wed and Thurs. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">             Last service departs Lampeter  13.45.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Trains</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> Four services per day at 4 hour intervals.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">1hr 30 mins to Swanse</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">a, last service departs at 18.21</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">2hrs 30mins to Shrewsbury, las</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">t service departs 18.05</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Link between train and bus service extremely poor.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">eg the bus to Brecon departs Llandovery train station at 10.40, the train arrives from Swansea at 10.37 allowing just 3mins for the connection.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">No connection if the train is late.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Lack of services</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> to/from nearby villages not on the A40 corridor.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Surrounding villages used to connect to Llandovery by the Post Bus.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Thi</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">s service has been discontinued</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">There are many villages and communities that have no access to public transport</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> at all.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none">4)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Resulting problems for the local community</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">:</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Young people </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">unable to access after school activities, no transport home.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">People out of work, school leavers, work placement people, those struggling with poor mental health issues and those wit</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">h physical and learning disabilities  - an efficient transport system would increase access to work opportunities for them.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">18-25 year olds have to pay a high premium for car insurance which restricts those who might have a car. The young who do not live </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">in towns are severely limited in their access to work, cultural activities and socialising. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Families – affected by cost of keeping a car on the road, eg  a two car family having to give up one car resulting in limitations on access to out of school activ</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">ities.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Able bodied adults who are non drivers have to rely on neighbours or expensive taxi services to travel into Llandovery, eg  £30 return fare from Rhandirmwyn to Llandovery</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> – a distance of seven miles.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Adults with mobility problems are dependant on </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">others being able to visit them for social and caring services.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 24pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:none">5)</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline"> </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline">Suggested solutions</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; text-decoration:underline"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Buses  - increase the number of services to</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> include evenings </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Trains – add one extra service per day in each direction</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> at appropriate times.</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Transport links – </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">realistic co-ordination of timetables, this should be feasible as both buses and trains are operated by Arriva.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Links to nearby villages – introduce a dial-up request mini-bus service.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">A service entitled Bwcabus operates in the western half of the county </span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">only. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">Rural areas require direct buses linking town to town centres, with feeder minibuses from surrounding villages. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">The times of trains and buses should facilitate work in the mornings and socialising in the evenings. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt 36pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Why in the 21</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:8pt; font-weight:bold; vertical-align:super">st</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> Century shoul</span><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">d people feel as though they are on house arrest simply because they do not have access to a set of wheels?</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:108%; margin:0pt 0pt 8pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>